    <name>
      <text>10.1.1.7 Equal complex numbers</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>If the two complex numbers \( z_1 = {@z1_r@}+{@z1_i*%i@} \) and \( z_2 = {@z2_r@}-{@z2_i*%i@}\) are equal then find the values of the real numbers \(k\) and \(l\).</p><p>\( k = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]</p><p>\( l = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt2]]<br></p><p>Give your answers as rational numbers.</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[Since \( z_1 = z_2 \) we can equate their real and imaginary parts. So:&nbsp;<p>\[ {@a@}k+{@b@} = k+ {@d@} \quad&nbsp; \text{and} \quad {@c@}l-{@d@} =&nbsp;-(k-l) \]</p><p>By solving these equations we find \( k = \displaystyle {@ta1@}\) and \(l = \displaystyle {@ta2@}\).</p><p><br></p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
